Camden is a town at a crossroads. A prestigious and agricultural based town, Camden is now on the very edge of Sydney's extensive urban sprawl.  The town still fiercely maintains is independent and country character, with a focus on its heritage, but it remains to be seen how long it can maintain this difference in the wave of development in Sydney's south west.
Camden is a short diversion from the M5 heading south from Sydney.  Regular bus services link Camden with Campbelltown station and Macarthur stations on the Cityrail network.
The town of Camden is small enough to walk.
